		"description": "<p>You are even more of a jack-of-all-trades than most bards, and are comfortable alone or in a crowd, in a settlement or in the wilderness. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Dexterity, Wisdom, or Charisma score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>Half your bard levels count as ranger levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.n83irh1dygryy7q8]{Stride and Seek} feature.</li>\n<li>Half your ranger levels count as bard levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.m7siz0z3rlng8h20]{Bardic Inspiration} feature.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with your choice of the Mirror&rsquo;s Glint, Mist and Shade, or Grinding Cog combat tradition and learn a 1st-degree maneuver from the chosen tradition. It does not count against your maneuvers known.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with a tool or musical instrument of your choice.</li>\n</ul>",
